text.tspan: The general rule must be something like:
Say you have a tensor (which could be a product of tensors)
and all their edges are connected, then you can pow(2).
I mean, this is easy to see, that sum_is G_i1,i2 G_i1,i2 ...
can be written as sum_is (G_i1,i2)^2 ... no matter what
other tensors might be "using" those same edges.
Really, the only "trick" is that edges that are _only_ used by
the two copies must have a copy / sum-dot added.
